title.narrative: PROGRAMMATIC ENVIRONMENT, POLICY/LEGAL FRAMEWORKS

description.narrative: By 2019, the programmatic environment at national and local levels is strengthened with adequate policy and legal frameworks in line with international standards., which contributes to Access To Justice, Evaluation, Evaluation (Covid), Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention Of Harmful Practice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid), Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, 70% of children (girls and boys), the most vulnerable in priority intervention areas, are protected from violence, including in emergency situations, and families adopt protective behaviours.

description.narrative: En 2021, le cadre juridique et programmatique du secteur de la protection de l’enfant en Guinée s&39;est enrichi avec la signature d’un nouvel arrêté interministériel pour renforcer l&39;interopérabilité entre les systèmes de protection de l&39;enfance, de santé et de justice. La perspective était d&39;améliorer l&39;accès des enfants vulnérables aux services sociaux de base, notamment l&39;enregistrement des naissances, la justice des enfants et les soins de santé. Avant cette signature, le secteur s’est doté d’un plan d’action quinquennal (2021-2025), à la suite du 2eme Forum national de l’enfance que l’UNICEF a soutenu techniquement et financièrement. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:02/02/2022
